Set the working directory and read in the data

setwd("~/data-viz/ebola")
data <- read.csv(file="Microbe-scope-bugs.csv", header=TRUE,na.strings = "NA")

Preparation. There are “” values.

library(ggplot2)
library(scales)
library(grid)

Clean the data.

Scope<-data[,c(1,2,4,5)]
scope<-Scope[-1,]
check<-complete.cases(scope)
sum(!check)
## [1] 0
scope=subset(scope,average.basic.reproductive.rate!=""&case.fatality.rate!=""&primary.mode.of.transmission!="")
#remove outliers
scope=scope[-grep("Malaria",scope$X),]
# scope=gsub("","NA",scope$)

Transform the data

contagious=as.numeric(as.character(scope$average.basic.reproductive.rate))
#Dealing with the %
deadliness=(as.numeric(gsub("%","",as.character(scope$case.fatality.rate))))/100
scope=cbind(scope,contagious,deadliness)

Plot the graph

base<-ggplot(data=scope,aes(x=contagious,y=deadliness,colour=primary.mode.of.transmission,ymax=max(deadliness)*1.2,ymin=0,xmin=0,xmax=20,label=X)) #difine ymax
p1<-base+geom_point(size=6)+geom_text(position="identity",hjust=-0.1,vjust=-1,size=4)
#position=dodge will remove the overlap point

#set the guides
#use element_text class
p2<-p1+guides(colour=guide_legend(title="RPIMARY TRANSMISSION METHOD",direction = "horizontal",label.theme=element_text(colour="dark grey",angle=0,size=10),keywidth = 1, keyheight = 1))

#set the x,y label and the graph title
p3<-p2+labs(list(title = "The Microbe-Scope", x = "CONTAGIOUSNESS", y = "DEADLINESS   \ncase fatality rate"))+scale_x_continuous(breaks=1:17,limits=c(0,20))+ scale_y_continuous(breaks=c(0.001,0.01,seq(from=0.1,to=1,by=0.1)),limits=c(0,1.2),labels = percent)

#y="log10"
#transformation to scale y
p4<-p3+coord_trans(y = "sqrt")

#add range partition line
#confliction between vline and the coord transformation
# p4<-p3+geom_vline(xintercept = 1,linetype="longdash",position="identity")
p5<-p4+geom_segment(x = 1, y = 0, xend = 1, yend = 1.2,colour="black")+geom_segment(x = 5, y = 0, xend = 5, yend = 1.2,colour="grey")+geom_segment(x = 7, y = 0, xend = 7, yend = 1.2,colour="grey")+geom_segment(x = 12, y = 0, xend = 12, yend = 1.2,colour="grey")+geom_segment(x = 0, y = 0.01, xend = 20, yend = 0.01,colour="black")

#add annotation
p6<-p5+annotate("text", x=c(0.3,3,6,9,15), y = 1.1, label = c("not very","quite contagious","very","highly","vaccinate now!"),colour="grey")+annotate("text",x=19,y=c(0.001,0.1,0.4,0.8),label=c("not too deadly\n highly risk groups\n(infants,the aged)","quite deadly\nunlucky or unhealthy","deadly\nhigh chance","extremely deadly\ndeath likely"),colour="grey")+annotate("rect", xmin = 0, xmax = 17, ymin = 0, ymax = 0.01,alpha =.2)+annotate("rect", xmin = 0, xmax = 17, ymin = 0.2, ymax = 0.5, alpha = .1)

#theme defines the global element effect
#unit class
p7<-p6+theme(panel.background = element_rect(fill = "white"),legend.position="top",legend.box="horizontal",legend.key.size=unit(x=1,units="npc"),plot.title=element_text(size=rel(1.5),colour="black",face="bold",hjust=-0.1),axis.title.x=element_text(colour="dark grey",face="bold"),axis.title.y=element_text(colour="dark grey",face="bold")) #relevant size
#show the result
p7
